#####################################################################
##                       1. PRESENTATION                           ##
#####################################################################

                          Charge Abe, discharge your brain, go party.

 *  Public install :    http://abe.rocknroot.org
 *  Homepage:           http://rocknroot.org/content/abe
 *  Version :           alpha - 0.1-Wilde

  Abe (Amazing Brain Expansion) is kind of a personnal encyclopedia
where you can throw notes and definitions and maybe organize them
later.

  You can also share some with friends, make them public and other
social stuff.

  Code is free, so if you're paranoid, you can install it at home or
in that little private internet of yours.

#####################################################################
##                       2. INSTALLATION                           ##
#####################################################################

  We asume that you already have a web server capable of running Ruby
on Rails applications (keywords : Apache, nginx, mod_passenger, ...).

 $ git clone git://github.com/Nekith/Abe.git abe
 $ cd abe
 - edit config/database.yml with coherent data
 # bundle install (execute this with root privileges)
 $ bundle exec rake db:create RAILS_ENV=production
 $ bundle exec rake db:migrate RAILS_ENV=production
 $ bundle exec rake assets:precompile RAILS_ENV=production
 - be patient...
 - restart web server (apachectl restart, ...)

